Redraw the shape each frame in `update()`, varying the parameters over time. Always call `clear()` first:

```typescript
class PulsingCircle extends cc.Layer {
    private _draw: cc.DrawNode;
    private _time: number = 0;
    private static readonly BASE_RADIUS = 40;
    private static readonly PULSE_AMOUNT = 15;
    private static readonly PULSE_SPEED = 3;

    onEnter(): void {
        super.onEnter();
        this._draw = new cc.DrawNode();
        this.addChild(this._draw);
        this.scheduleUpdate();
    }

    update(dt: number): void {
        this._time += dt;
        this._draw.clear();

        const radius = PulsingCircle.BASE_RADIUS +
            Math.sin(this._time * PulsingCircle.PULSE_SPEED) * PulsingCircle.PULSE_AMOUNT;

        const alpha = Math.floor(128 + 127 * Math.sin(this._time * PulsingCircle.PULSE_SPEED));

        this._draw.drawDot(
            cc.p(240, 160),
            radius,
            cc.color(0, 200, 255, alpha)
        );

        this._draw.drawCircle(
            cc.p(240, 160), radius, 0, 32,
            false, 2, cc.color(0, 255, 255, 255)
        );
    }
}
```

The pattern: `scheduleUpdate()` -> `update()` calls `clear()` then redraws with time-varying parameters. This works for any animated shape — just change the position, size, color, or vertex positions based on `this._time`.

