`cc.sys.restartVM()` restarts the JavaScript virtual machine on native (JSB) platforms:

```typescript
cc.sys.restartVM(): void  // JSB only, no-op on H5
```

This completely resets the JS runtime, re-executing all scripts from scratch. Use cases:

```typescript
// Hot reload during development
function devReload(): void {
    if (cc.sys.isNative) {
        cc.log('Restarting VM for hot reload...');
        cc.sys.restartVM();
    } else {
        // On web, just reload the page
        window.location.reload();
    }
}

// Recovery from unrecoverable error
function handleFatalError(error: Error): void {
    cc.error('Fatal error:', error.message);
    // Save state first
    cc.sys.localStorage.setItem('crash_recovery', 'true');
    if (cc.sys.isNative) {
        cc.sys.restartVM();
    }
}

// Language change that requires full restart
function changeLanguage(lang: string): void {
    cc.sys.localStorage.setItem('language', lang);
    if (cc.sys.isNative) {
        cc.sys.restartVM(); // restart to reload all assets in new language
    }
}
```

**Warning:** This destroys ALL JavaScript state — all variables, objects, listeners, and timers are lost. Only use as a last resort. Always save critical state to localStorage before calling.

Use different strategies depending on the search:

```typescript
// 1. Direct child by tag (O(n) on children count)
const child = parent.getChildByTag(42);

// 2. Direct child by name (O(n) on children count)
const named = parent.getChildByName('player');

// 3. Deep recursive search by name
let found: cc.Node | null = null;
root.enumerateChildren('//player', (node) => {
    found = node;
    return true; // stop on first match
});

// 4. Maintain your own lookup map for O(1) access
class NodeRegistry {
    private static map: Map<string, cc.Node> = new Map();

    static register(key: string, node: cc.Node): void {
        this.map.set(key, node);
    }

    static unregister(key: string): void {
        this.map.delete(key);
    }

    static get(key: string): cc.Node | undefined {
        return this.map.get(key);
    }
}

// Register on creation
NodeRegistry.register('player', playerNode);
// Fast lookup
const player = NodeRegistry.get('player');
```

For large scenes, maintain a registry rather than searching the tree every frame.

